1. DEFINITIONS

   "Software" means the Wisdom Layer SDK, including all compiled
   binaries (including compiled _internal modules) distributed in
   the Python package "wisdom-layer" and on https://wisdomlayer.ai.
   Sample code in the examples/ directory and documentation in the
   docs/ directory may be freely used and adapted in Licensee's own
   projects.

   "Licensee" means the individual or legal entity installing, using,
   or integrating the Software.

   "License Key" means the opaque token issued by the Wisdom Layer
   licensing service that, when supplied to the Software at runtime,
   determines which tier of features the Licensee may use.

   "Tier" means the feature set and use rights unlocked by a given
   License Key: Free, Pro, Team, Business, or Enterprise. Tier limits
   are enforced at runtime by the Software; tier-conditioned use
   rights (including but not limited to customer-facing, multi-tenant,
   embedded, white-label, and OEM deployment rights) are governed by
   this License and the applicable subscription agreement.

2. GRANT

   Subject to Licensee's compliance with this License, Rhatigan AGI
   LLC (d/b/a Rhatigan Labs) grants Licensee a non-exclusive, non-transferable,
   non-sublicensable right to install and use the Software inside
   Licensee's own applications, solely for the purposes permitted by
   Licensee's active Tier.

3. TIER LIMITS

   Free Tier: permitted for personal, evaluation, and small-scale
   internal use subject to the runtime-enforced limits documented at
   https://wisdomlayer.ai/pricing. To upgrade, visit
   https://wisdomlayer.ai/pricing or contact jeff@rhatigan.ai.

   Pro, Team, and Business Tiers: licensed for internal tools and
   production systems the Licensee operates; Pro is one (1) developer
   seat, Team is up to ten (10) seats, Business is up to fifty (50)
   seats; all three share an identical SDK feature set. Customer-
   facing, multi-tenant, embedded, white-label, OEM, or otherwise
   end-user-serving deployments require an Enterprise license.
   Governed by the subscription agreement between Licensee and
   Rhatigan AGI LLC. Seat counts, agent counts, and feature access
   follow the active subscription; Licensee's License Key is revoked
   on material non-payment after the grace period set forth in that
   agreement.

   Enterprise Tier: required whenever an agent serves an end user
   other than the Licensee, including customer-facing products,
   multi-tenant deployments, embedded / white-label / OEM
   distribution inside another product, and regulated environments
   that require contractual intellectual-property, audit, or service-
   level terms. Includes unlimited developer seats, custom storage
   backends, air-gapped operation, and the contractual terms set
   forth in the applicable master services agreement. Negotiated per
   contract.

